	(9978,1079,'content_0_content','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Protect The Goal Campaign is an initiative of UNAIDS that uses the power of sports and culture to reach: zero new HIV infections; zero discrimination; and zero AIDS-related deaths.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Ambassador Mensima Clerk CEO and Founder of Kunim Foundation Ghana who is on her Tour To Africa paid a courtesy visit to Reach A Hand Uganda</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Campaign is aimed at</span></p>\r\n Using of the popularity and convening power of sports to unite the world for the goal of an AIDS-free generation;\r\n Raising awareness and advocacy for the UNAIDS vision of zero new HIV infections; zero discrimination; and zero AIDS-related deaths; and\r\n Mobilize the worlds of sports and culture to strengthen the AIDS response and accelerate progress in HIV prevention, and reproductive health, particularly among young people.'),
