	(10954,1153,'content_0_content','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The <a href=\"http://www.reachahand.org/index.php/projects/125-peer-educators-academy-pea\"><span class=\"s2\">Peer Educators Academy</span></a> 2015 fellows (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/PEA2015?src=hash\"><span class=\"s3\">#PEA2015</span></a>) are a unique and amazing group of young people, who weve seen growing to highly informed bold communicators, problem solvers, creative thinkers and good reproductive health advocates.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s3\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/PEA2015?src=hash\">#PEA2015</a></span><span class=\"s1\">Peer Educators have carried out numerous school outreaches since they were passed out of the Academy. During these outreaches, they carried out Focus Group Discussions where the they had break away sessions with the young people in the schools and they discussed SRHR topics that directly affect the in-school young people. These topics cut across from body changes, sex and relationships, teenage pregnancy and abortion, pornography, drug and substance abuse, peer pressure, career development, HIV/AIDS as well as life skills.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1154\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"430\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1154\" src=\"http://s194518.gridserver.com/rahu/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Madrine-Peer-Educator-2015.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"430\" height=\"287\" /> Madrine, Peer Educator 2015, conducting a Focused Group Discussion.[/caption]\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">After the group sessions, the young people in the schools came together and participated in the edutainment. During this activity, the young people got an opportunity to depict the major SRHR themes in their schools in the form of role play in dramas. These dramas were developed with the help of the peer educators assigned to the school. Our cultural icons gave motivational talks to the young people </span><span class=\"s2\">using their life experiences to encourage them make life choices from an informed perspective</span><span class=\"s1\">. These included; Dr. Naboth Cole, Dr. Christine Mbabazi, Tiwa Savage, Maurice Hasa and Ray Signature. Comedians like Prince Emma, McVex and Salvador shared rib cracking jokes with the young people and also each gave them a take home message about relationships and sex, basing on their personal experiences.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1155\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"430\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1155\" src=\"http://s194518.gridserver.com/rahu/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Dr-Christine.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"430\" height=\"287\" /> Dr. Christine addressing young people at Bishop Cipriano Kihangire[/caption]\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Over time, a total of 909 young people received HIV Counselling and Testing services at the outreaches. Students who participated in the RAHU Inter-school Drama Competitions, were awarded with certificates of participation during the school outreaches.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1156\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"430\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1156 size-full\" src=\"http://s194518.gridserver.com/rahu/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Young-person-receiving-HCT-services.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"430\" height=\"287\" /> Young person receiving HCT services at a school outreach.[/caption]\r\n\r\nSchool outreaches carried out were in Lowell Girls School, Mariam High School, Bethany High School, Katale Modern School, Bishop Cipriano Kihangire Day School, Bishop Cipriano Boarding School, Hana Mixed School, Kisubi Mapeera Secondary school, Atlas High School, Mbogo High School, Kamda Community School, Mpuuge Seed Secondary school and Kiwoko Secondary School.\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Watch highlights of one of our outreaches at Mariam High School:</span></p>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/frNEqdx_g2w\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">To be part of our GYMO journey come 2016, please enroll for our upcoming Peer Educators Academy. Look out: we are soon calling for applications.</span></p>'),
